AIM: The Tokuhashi prognosis score consists of six parameters. The sum of points 
rated for each parameter can be correlated with the prognosis. This study 
evaluates the score variations that have been done by different authors and 
Tokuhashi et al. themselves.
METHODS: Two hundred and seventeen consecutive patients, surgically treated for 
vertebral metastases, were studied retrospectively. We calculated the original 
and modified score of Tokuhashi and evaluated the predictive value for the 
individual life expectancy.
